21/06/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A three-day forum on NATO's security in the Black Sea region began in Sofia Tuesday (21 June). The George C. Marshall European Centre for Strategic Studies and the Bulgarian Ministry of Defence co-organised the event, which includes representatives of NATO members Bulgaria, Greece, Romania and Turkey as well as security experts from the United States. Participants will also discuss ways to enhance regional co-operation. (Bulgarian National Radio - 21/06/05)
